(Thirsty-Lang (Specification (v3.5)))

# ============================================================================ #
# STATUS: ACTIVE | TIER: MASTER | DATE: 2026-03-11                             #
# COMPLIANCE: Sovereign-Native / TSCG-B                                        #
# ============================================================================ #

## 1. Core Grammar
Thirsty-Lang uses a recursive symbolic structure based on nested S-expressions.
Syntax: `(Operator (Argument1 (Argument2 ...)))`

## 2. TSCG-B Opcode Mapping
The following table defines the symbolic-to-binary mapping used for high-density encapsulation.

| Symbol       | Opcode (HEX) | Description                                  |
|--------------|--------------|----------------------------------------------|
| `Project-AI` | `0x01`       | System Root Anchor                           |
| `Status`     | `0x02`       | State Declaration                            |
| `Active`     | `0x03`       | Operation: ACTIVE                            |
| `HALT`       | `0x04`       | Enforcement: Termination                     |
| `Audit`      | `0x05`       | Logic Trace Trigger                          |
| `Bridge`     | `0x06`       | Host Interface Binding                       |
| `TARL`       | `0x07`       | Active Resistance Logic Block                |
| `TSCG-B`     | `0x08`       | Binary Compression Layer                     |
| `Sovereign`  | `0x09`       | Master Tier Integrity Level                  |
| `AI-Model`   | `0x0A`       | Neural Compute Signal                        |

## 3. T.A.R.L. Resistance Logic
The Logical NOT of unauthorized mutation. 
Formula: `R = (Integ(S) == Master) ? Pass : (HALT && Audit)`

## 4. Execution Model
Thirsty-Lang code is interpreted by the `Native Bridge` or compiled directly into a `.tscgb` binary core.

(End (Specification))
